<subSubSection id="CAB177B53F24EE3BFF60104AB636FA35" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8214243E3F24EE3BFF60104AB636FA35" blockId="50.[192,1440,1283,1467]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B0DFF82C3F24EE3BFF60104AB629FA95" bold="true" box="[192,351,1283,1307]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Discussion.</emphasis>
In their review of 
<collectingRegion id="406FEADC3F24EE3BFDE0104AB5EDFA95" box="[576,667,1283,1307]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Florida</collectingRegion>
ceratopogonids, 
<bibRefCitation id="E63A59CF3F24EE3BFCCA104AB3F5FA95" author="Wilkening, A. J. &amp; D. L. Kline &amp; W. W. Wirth" box="[874,1155,1283,1307]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" pagination="511 - 537" refId="ref37442" refString="Wilkening, A. J., D. L. Kline, and W. W. Wirth. 1985. An annotated checklist of the Ceratopogonidae (Diptera) of Florida with a new synonymy. Florida Entomologist 68: 511 - 537." type="journal article" year="1985">Wilkening et al. (1985)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="45AB5FBD3F24EE3BFB75104DB216FA95" box="[1237,1376,1283,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis id="B0DFF82C3F24EE3BFB75104DB216FA95" box="[1237,1376,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">B. pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but, they noted that 
<collectingRegion id="406FEADC3F24EE3BFE2A106AB693FAB5" box="[394,485,1315,1339]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Florida</collectingRegion>
records were not available for this species, and a study in progress by WLG confirms this. Therefore, we have deleted this species from the ceratopogonid fauna of 
<collectingRegion id="406FEADC3F24EE3BFB66100AB255FAD5" box="[1222,1315,1347,1371]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Florida</collectingRegion>
. However, USNM specimens of the 
<taxonomicName id="45AB5FBD3F24EE3BFE7D102DB517FAF5" box="[477,609,1379,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis id="B0DFF82C3F24EE3BFE7D102DB517FAF5" box="[477,609,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">B. pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex include three species described prior to the study by Wilkening et al. as well as several other undescribed species (see accounts of 
<emphasis id="B0DFF82C3F24EE3BFBA410CDB230FA15" box="[1028,1350,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName id="45AB5FBD3F24EE3BFBA410CDB3CAFA15" box="[1028,1212,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laciniastyla">B. laciniastyla</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="45AB5FBD3F24EE3BFB6910CDB230FA15" box="[1225,1350,1412,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spicata">B. spicata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45AB5FBD3F24EE3BFA2510CDB646FA35" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncistyla">
<emphasis id="B0DFF82C3F24EE3BFA2510CDB646FA35" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">B. uncistyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
